The Erdős Frontier Atlas — hub index (atlas/stubs.json)
=======================================================

The machine-readable hub index (atlas/stubs.json) is compiled by
tools/build_stubs.py from the following Apache-2.0 licensed sources. Their
content is used under the terms of the Apache License, Version 2.0. Each stub
record carries per-source provenance (repo, file, commit SHA, SPDX license).

1. teorth/erdosproblems  (https://github.com/teorth/erdosproblems)
   Erdős problems database contributors (incl. Thomas Bloom and Terence Tao).
   Used: data/problems.yaml — problem number, prize, status, OEIS, tags,
   formalization flag. Licensed under Apache-2.0.

2. google-deepmind/formal-conjectures
   (https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures)
   The Formal Conjectures Authors.
   Used: FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/*.lean — informal problem statements
   (docstrings) and formalization metadata for the formalized subset.
   Licensed under Apache-2.0.

erdosproblems.com (Thomas Bloom) is the canonical HUMAN index of the Erdős
problems. This repository is its computational annex: it LINKS to each problem
at erdosproblems.com/N and never crawls, copies, or re-hosts prose from that
site. Its robots.txt (ai-train=no; use=reference) is respected. Problems for
which no Apache-2.0 statement exists carry statement=null and a link only.

Verified frontier records produced here are contributed back upstream through
the maintainers' sanctioned channels (the teorth/erdosproblems repository and
erdosproblems.com), never intercepted or re-hosted.
